09/05/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police have busted a criminal group involved in credit card fraud, the Interior Ministry announced on Sunday (May 8th). 
Three Macedonian citizens and a Serb were detained during the operation conducted with Serbia's Interior Ministry. 
The group was allegedly using forged credit cards and fake ID cards to make illegal transactions in Macedonia, Serbia and Bosnia and Herzegovina. 
(Makfax, MIA - 08/05/11)
